<subsubsection><title>Add or subtract algebraic fractions</title>

<assemblage><title>To add or subtract unlike fractions</title><p><ol marker="1">
<li>Find the LCD for the fractions.</li>
<li>Build each fraction to an equivalent one with the LCD as its denominator.</li>
<li>Add or subtract the numerators. Keep the same denominator.</li></ol></p></assemblage>

<example><statement><p>Subtract <m>~\dfrac{2x}{w} - \dfrac{3x}{w}</m></p></statement>

<solution><p>These are like fractions, so we need only combine their numerators.
    <me>\dfrac{2x}{w} - \dfrac{3x}{w} = \dfrac{2x-3x}{w} = \dfrac{-x}{w}</me></p></solution></example>

<example><statement><p>Subtract <m>~\dfrac{3}{a} - \dfrac{a+2}{a}</m></p></statement>

<solution><p>These are like fractions, so we need only combine their numerators. Be careful to subtract both terms of the second numerator.
    <me>\dfrac{3}{a} - \dfrac{a+2}{a} = \dfrac{3-(a+2)}{a} = \dfrac{1-a}{a}</me></p></solution></example>

<example><statement><p>Add <m>~2 + \dfrac{1}{x}</m></p></statement>

<solution><p>We write 2 as a fraction, <m>\dfrac{2}{1}</m>, and build it to the LCD, <m>x</m>.
    <me>\dfrac{2}{1} \cdot \alert{\dfrac{x}{x}} + \dfrac{1}{x} = \dfrac{2x}{x}  + \dfrac{1}{x} = \dfrac{2x+1}{x}</me></p>
</solution></example>

